<html aria-label=3D"message body"><head><meta http-equiv=3D"content-type" =
content=3D"text/html; charset=3Dutf-8"></head><body =
style=3D"overflow-wrap: break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; =
line-break: after-white-space;"><div dir=3D"auto" style=3D"overflow-wrap: =
break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; line-break: after-white-space;"><p =
data-start=3D"674" data-end=3D"683">Hi Lance,</p><p data-start=3D"685" =
data-end=3D"791">Thank you for your response and for arranging the =
payment of the remaining temporary accommodation amount.</p><p =
data-start=3D"793" data-end=3D"963">I would however like to clarify a =
few points regarding the storage of contents, the condition of the =
property, and the veterinary expenses that were submitted =
previously.</p><p data-start=3D"965" data-end=3D"1337">Firstly, the =
property&nbsp;<b>is not alarmed, it&nbsp;</b><strong data-start=3D"987" =
data-end=3D"1036">does not currently have electricity =
connected</strong>, as it was disconnected following the fire by Fire =
and Emergency during the incident. For this reason, I was somewhat =
surprised to read that it had been understood to be alarmed, and I would =
appreciate clarification as to how that conclusion was reached.</p><p =
data-start=3D"1339" data-end=3D"1455">Secondly, the property =
remains&nbsp;<strong data-start=3D"1370" =
data-end=3D"1392">smoke-contaminated</strong>, including areas upstairs, =
even several months after the fire.</p><p data-start=3D"1457" =
data-end=3D"2009">As I am now responsible for arranging and covering =
the&nbsp;<strong data-start=3D"1596" data-end=3D"1649">decontamination =
or disposal of the salvaged items</strong>, asking me to move those =
items back into a property that is&nbsp;<strong data-start=3D"1734" =
data-end=3D"1841">not habitable, without electricity, not alarmed, and =
still affected by smoke and chemical contamination</strong>&nbsp;appears =
<b>unreasonable</b> and <b>inconsistent with</b>&nbsp;<strong =
data-start=3D"1885" data-end=3D"1924">fair and reasonable claims =
handling</strong>, particularly as it exposes the items to further =
risks, &nbsp;contamination and damage.</p><p data-start=3D"2011" =
data-end=3D"2518">In addition, storing contents in a fire-affected =
structure that has not been decontaminated does not appear consistent =
with the purpose of the policy benefit covering&nbsp;<strong =
data-start=3D"2178" data-end=3D"2221">temporary storage after an insured =
loss</strong>, which exists to protect contents while the house is being =
made habitable. The contents policy wording provides cover for the =
reasonable costs of storing contents when they need to be removed =
following an insured loss while the house is being made =
habitable.&nbsp;</p><p data-start=3D"2771" data-end=3D"3147">Regarding =
the <b>veterinary expenses,</b> I submitted the reimbursement request =
for NZD 395.85 on 9 October, following a discussion with the <b>previous =
claim manager</b> who <b>verbally approved</b> the reimbursement and =
asked me to provide the invoice or bank statement/proof as proof of the =
expense.For this reason, receiving a different position more than five =
months after the request was submitted is somewhat unexpected and =
contradicting the verbal approval and previous guidance.</p><p =
data-start=3D"3621" data-end=3D"3781">Given that as insurers iou are =
required to handle claims fairly and within a reasonable timeframe, I =
would appreciate a reconsideration of both matters.</p><p =
data-start=3D"3783" data-end=3D"3815">I look forward to your =
response.</p><p data-start=3D"3817" data-end=3D"3842">Kind regards,<br =
data-start=3D"3830" data-end=3D"3833">Raffaella</p><p data-start=3D"3817" =
data-end=3D"3842"><br></p><div><blockquote type=3D"cite"><div>On 12 Mar =
2026, at 1:22=E2=80=AFPM, Lance O'Riley &lt;Lance.ORiley@tower.co.nz&gt; =
wrote:</div><br class=3D"Apple-interchange-newline"><div><meta =
charset=3D"UTF-8"><div class=3D"WordSection1" style=3D"page: =
